<TITLE> Nepal bus catches fire, at least 7 dead: police </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 KATHMANDU, Jan 18 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - At least seven people were killed and 22 injured on Friday after a bus caught fire in southern Nepal, police said. The independent Kantipur radio said there had been an explosion on the bus and that 10 people had died. It gave no details. The bus was travelling from Janakpur to Birgunj in the southern plains of Nepal when it caught fire about 80 km (50 miles) southeast of Kathmandu, a police officer said. "We have reports that the bus caught fire. Details are awaited," police officer Krishna Kunwar said. Nepal's southern plains have been rocked by ethnic tensions and violence by several armed groups seeking regional autonomy. Scores of people were killed in the tension in the area last ye
